# logic-workbook

![problems](https://img.shields.io/badge/300%2B_problems-logic-7F77DD?style=flat-square)
![status](https://img.shields.io/badge/status-in_progress-1D9E75?style=flat-square)
![language-agnostic](https://img.shields.io/badge/language-agnostic-888780?style=flat-square)

A structured workbook of 300+ logic-building exercises that develop the mental models required for Data Structures & Algorithms — from boolean decisions to integrated applied logic.

> Part of [Data-Structure-And-Algorithm](https://github.com/rajan21045/Data-Structure-And-Algorithm)

---

## About

This folder tracks my progress through *The Programming Logic Workbook*. Solutions are language-agnostic in logic but implemented in the language of my choice per gate. The goal isn't syntax — it's building the ability to think in steps before writing a single line of code.

---

## Approach

- Logic over syntax — understand the *why* before the *how*
- 10 problems per day — consistency beats intensity
- Reduce steps — optimize after you solve

---

## Structure

| Gate | Topic | Problems |
|------|-------|----------|
| Gate 1 | Decisions & Boolean Logic | Q1 – Q50 |
| Gate 2 | Repetition & Iterative Flows | Q51 – Q100 |
| Gate 3 | Recursive Logic Patterns | Q101 – Q140 |
| Gate 4 | Linear Data Logic (Arrays) | Q141 – Q190 |
| Gate 5 | Text Processing Logic (Strings) | Q191 – Q240 |
| Gate 6 | Integrated Applied Logic | Q241 – Q300 |

---

## 30-Day Plan

| Phase | Focus | Target |
|-------|-------|--------|
| Days 1–5 | Decision Making | 10 q/day |
| Days 6–10 | Iteration & Loops | 10 q/day |
| Days 11–15 | Recursive Thinking | 8 q/day |
| Days 16–20 | Array Manipulation | 10 q/day |
| Days 21–25 | String Processing | 10 q/day |
| Days 26–30 | Integrated Logic | 12 q/day |

